    <item>
      <title>Tales from Willow Valley: The Smell of Adventure</title>
      <author> JustASmallTownVal </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1265337/tales-from-willow-valley-the-smell-of-adventure/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1265337-tales-from-willow-valley-the-smell-of-adventure/chapter/1265363/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">4d19a89071222f10ac4535a737a3fffb785ac1e5</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 18 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Paige is a new arrival in the town of Willow Valley, and is still tentatively getting her paws on the ground when she decides to take a step forward by going out for the day which causes her to cross paths with Aster, an intimidating and muscle-bound mommy domme who immediately sniffs out Paige as someone she might get along with. Follow along with Paige and Aster as they join each other on an average day in Willow Valley, and all that that implies.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This story is inspired by the world and characters created by Willow "Glopossum" and is a blatant piece of self-insert fanfiction featuring my Pallas's Catgirl Paige and Willow's cheetah Aster, my favorite character of hers, in addition to appearances every other major character in her world's canon. Many thanks to Willow for creating such a rich and diverse world of smut and for allowing me use of her characters in this story. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Additional thanks to:&lt;br /&gt; TrevorWolf for letting me feature his sona, as well as for his deep knowledge of Willow Valley lore to provide editing support and encouragement.&lt;br /&gt; Izzy "CornDogCanine" for additional editing support and encouragement.&lt;br /&gt; Aristidexo for use of her character Caroline.&lt;br /&gt; Maedog &amp; Colfox for the use of their sonas.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1265337-tales-from-willow-valley-the-smell-of-adventure/chapter/1265363/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Part 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I look up from my phone as I feel the bus slowly grind its brakes to a halt, the forward momentum jerking me and all the other passengers slightly forward once it does. Confirming the address listed on the display, I squeeze my way through the mass of bodies as a flow of passengers gently surges forward to make their way off onto the sidewalk. Disembarking, I take an apprehensive look up and down the block before sitting down on a bench to get my bearings and figure out which direction to head in. It may have only been a week since I arrived in Willow Valley but it’s still my first time actually venturing into the city itself proper since moving here, and that prospect is as exciting as it is deeply fucking terrifying, which is to say fully and completely. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It’s a nice enough morning; the sun is out, there aren’t too many people around and there’s a pleasant breeze in the air that cuts down on the otherwise sweltering heat just enough, but my mind is in places other than the weather. I’ve not only got to register myself at a new gym, which involves a short interview for membership approval that has me all manner of anxious already, I’ve got to then actually go and become part of said gym and try to not fail at attending regularly like I’ve done every time I’ve tried so far. I just have to go in there alone when there’s absolutely no one else who I can possibly try to connect and talk with to help make the experience even slightly bearable. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Once my phone blessedly gives me the direction to head in, my mind clears of its rapidly spiraling thoughts and I start down the path at once. Walking helps clear my mind even further as I press forward and take in my surroundings, marveling at the amount of foliage and greenery present compared to literally any other urban environment I’ve found myself in before. It feels like the person in charge of planning and development had quite the green thumb and wanted everyone else to enjoy it, urban sprawl be damned. It all lends a very pleasant aroma to the air that helps offset the typical city smell that I can still sense hanging around, but very much in the margins instead of at the front. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It’s at this point that I suddenly smell something else in the air, something a bit more potent and unmistakable, yet highly desirable and alluring. I give another few sniffs to confirm it is in fact coffee and as I snap my head to the right I quickly identify the source, which is a modest seeming building with a green roof slanting upward until it juts off the building itself, creating a covered seating area in the process. As if by instinct my path is diverted from the direction of the gym and towards this newfound oasis; I’d been a bit late getting up this morning and hadn’t had time to make myself any coffee, so this is a more than welcome sight to be sure. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Approaching the door I start to see more of the inside of the shop through its windows, along with the rather sizable number of bodies occupying it. My anxiety surges forth again and I stop in my tracks, frozen in place for what feels like an eternity. As I’m contemplating my options, those being to either run in the direction of a hopefully less crowded coffee shop or throwing caution to the wind and diving in feet first, the decision gets taken out of my hands as the door opens and from out behind it steps a young possum woman with a septum piercing, a mess of wavy brown hair, and the faintest wisps of a mustache dressed in a modest black blouse, lavender cardigan, and green loose-fitting pants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Seeing me standing near the doorway she gives me a smile and moves to hold the door open just enough for me to slip in as she exits. There’s something warm in her smile, something that helps put me at ease the moment I see it. It almost feels like she’s inviting me inside, and that there’s no need to worry. For the first time since arriving in Willow Valley I feel welcome, and like I don’t have anything to worry about.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I return the smile along with a small wave as I slide inside, taking stock of my surroundings once I’m in. It’s decorated rather simply with lots of hanging and potted plants instead of artwork, but it has warm peach colored walls that provide a lovely compliment to the greenery and has a very homey, welcoming atmosphere. It’s not the biggest coffee shop in the world but it still has plenty of room for tables, chairs, and booths for a sizable number of people to occupy, which unfortunately doesn’t stop them from pretty much all being occupied. A quick look to the right confirms all the tables are packed full, same with the booths on the left. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I grumble quietly to myself before stepping up to the counter, which thankfully isn’t busy at all, and hold my hand up in an attempt to wave down the lone member of the staff I notice, a short silver and black fox wearing a tight black halter-top and with an inscrutable expression on his face, laser focused on his phone and texting furiously. However, I barely manage to raise my hand past my head before into my immediate field of vision slides a young sand cat with pierced ears wearing a hot-pink muscle-tee and blue bike shorts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Heeeyy, welcome to The Nest!” he says with an almost inhuman level of perkiness for this early in the morning. “My name’s Junip, how can I help you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I start back a half step with a bit of a jump. His appearance was so sudden that I hadn’t even known he was there before he popped into my line of sight and it took my breath away momentarily.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh! Uhh…” I blanch at the question, my thoughts suddenly pushed to the side as I more fully take in Junip’s appearance. Not only is he dressed in clothing so tight it looks like it was painted on him, he also happens to be wearing eyeliner, mascara, and muted dark red lipstick, all of it impeccably detailed and making me feel a tad embarrassed that I didn’t even bother with my makeup at all this morning. At first glance I even think I see a hint of smoky eyeshadow until realizing it’s just his fur patterns.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Also, the tightness of his clothing reveals his modest but not insubstantial physique a little too completely, specifically where the bike shorts are concerned of which there is nothing modest or insubstantial in the slightest. I realize it’s been about four seconds of me just staring at that particular region of him before my brain suddenly formulates an actual thought.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uhh, yeah, I was uhh… I wanted to get an, uhh…” Unsurprisingly, my brain is still a bit jumbled from the suddenness of this encounter, which thankfully Junip picks up on.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Heh, it’s ok if you don’t know what you want right away! I know that our menu can be a tad overwhelming at first but you’ll get the hang of it eventually! Are you new in town?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I nod, grateful for this boy’s saintly patience. “Yeah, moved into my place about a week ago. Haven’t really gotten out at all because I wanted to get settled first but I started getting restless the other day, and I figured today should be the day I get out and start doing things.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Junip smiles so brightly he could light up a room from across a hallway. “Hell yeah! That’s awesome to hear, and welcome to Willow Valley! We’ve got a lot of great people here and I’m sure if you hang around long enough you’ll get to meet all of them at some point or another! Heck, you’ve already started.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He winks in the most unsubtle manner I’ve ever seen anyone do, which is enough to elicit a chuckle out of me in the process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Heh, I guess so,” I say as I start feeling a bit more at ease. “I really am excited to get to know this place better, it always seemed so cool from a distance and the testimonials from people I trust all point to it having a great night life.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Junip leans across the counter in about the most suggestive way possible, fixing me with a devious grin as he does with his tail coyly flitting back and forth. “Oh, you have no idea hun. This town gets absolutely &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;wild&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; when the sun goes down, and there’s lots to do if you know the right people to talk to. I could certainly help you out in that regard if you ever wanted it.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He cocks an eyebrow at me, his grin widening with each second. Through the sudden rush of horny feelings currently flooding my brain, both from the implications of Junip’s words and Junip himself, I suddenly remember why I came here in the first place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uhh….” I croak out with great effort. “You’ve got coffee here right?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Certainly!” Junip perks up again and resumes his customer-service veneer in a flash. “What did you want? We’ve got all the regular options plus a bevy of custom house specials, and I must say that our daily special today is absolutely to die for!” He delicately taps the small chalkboard sign sitting next to the register. I shake my head without even looking at it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, I’ll just stick with a 16oz Americano, with room.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I’ve never seen a sand cat pout so pathetically until this point. “Are you sure? That special is really good, and…” His eyes widen into a perfectly heartstring-tugging kitty-cat stare, “I spent so much time working on it too.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It takes every inch of me to not fall for this incredibly obvious play on my sympathies, and I only barely scrape by in the process. “I… uh, sorry but I’m kinda boring when it comes to my coffee orders in general, and I’m just not really feeling too adventurous today.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Junip rolls his eyes and lets out a defeated and annoyed sigh, before a thought visibly strikes him and he grins at me again. “Tell ya what, if you order the special I’ll pay for it and that way if you hate it you’re not out anything! I’ll even throw in a pastry just to sweeten the deal! Consider it a welcoming gift!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He taps on the glass of the display case, indicating the rows of baked goods lining the interior. I look down at the window, then back up at Junip who is fixing me with the most smug expression I’ve ever seen in my life. I want so deeply to be frustrated with him and yet there’s something about his relentlessly cheery and accommodating nature that makes it an impossibility. Plus, I’ve never &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;not&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; been one to be won over with the offer of free shit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I… well, heck why not,” I say with an only slightly resigned tone. “Let’s be adventurous today. I’ll take it, and I’ll go with the pão de queijo as well.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Excellent choice, I just made those for the first time today and I think they came out quite well, if I do say so myself!” Junip gives a couple quick snaps of his fingers in the direction of the fox, who looks up from his phone with an annoyed glower which Junip doesn’t seem to register one bit. “Business for you Casper, this lovely lady will take a 16oz of the daily special!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Casper rolls his eyes as he stuffs his phone back in his pocket and heads to the espresso machine without a word, grabbing a portafilter and getting to work. Junip, meanwhile, turns back towards me with a satisfied expression. “Will that be for here or to go?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I take another look around the room, every table and booth still occupied by at least one other person, before turning back. “Well, I usually take my coffee to stay but it looks like that’s not much of an option today.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Junip takes a look around the place himself before settling on something that draws another grin out of him. “That table, right there. He won’t mind.” He points to a table stationed in the middle of the floor to my immediate left, which happens to be occupied by a brown wolf with an undercut, wearing a tight turquoise t-shirt and a black velvet choker, his nose buried in a book. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I turn back to Junip with a dubious eyebrow raised, which brings back that smug grin of his. “Oh don’t worry, they won’t bite. Trust me, I know from experience.” Junip winks again, followed by a soft chuckle as he snatches the pastry from the display case and sticks it on a small plate. “Just let him know I sent you over, he’ll make space.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I shrug my shoulders as I take the plate from him, fully on board with whatever at this point. “If you say so.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He chuckles again. “Oh, but I do.” He gives a subtle wave in the wolf’s direction. “Go on over and make a new friend, I’ll bring out your coffee when it’s ready.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I smile even in spite of the suddenness of each new development; normally I would be running for the hills after the first slight deviation from my comfort zone but there’s something about this place that feels incredibly disarming and quells any anxiety I’d usually have. As I approach the table the wolf gazes up at me with a questioning look on his face.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, uh, hey there,” I say with obvious embarrassment. “Junip said that…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The name seems to shoot through him like a bolt of lightning and his demeanor changes in a fraction of a second. “Oh! Yes, by all means, take a seat!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Breathing a sigh of relief I pull the chair on the opposing end of the table out and slide my tail through the opening before plopping down. I look across the table at the wolf for a few seconds before realizing I should probably introduce myself and extending my hand to him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uhh, hi there, my name’s Paige.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He eagerly grabs it and shakes enthusiastically. “Mine’s Trevor! Call me Trev. It’s nice to meet you, Paige!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I question whether or not this level of enthusiasm is a normal trait among everyone in Willow Valley, or if it just comes naturally after being in Junip’s presence for long enough.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well it’s nice to meet you, Trev.” I let go of his hand and return it to the strap of my handbag, fiddling with it nervously. “I must say I didn’t quite expect my first day in the city to involve meeting someone like this.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor perks up as he sets his book down to fully turn his attention to me. “A newcomer eh? Well, you sure picked the right place to land!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I chuckle dryly. “Yeah, that’s what people seem to be telling me. It certainly seemed like an enticing upgrade from the small town life I thought I was gonna be stuck in forever, but everything about this place seemed like it was the right choice for me in general. Doesn’t feel like I was misled in that assumption so far.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor nods his head vigorously. “You got that right, alright! I’ve been here about three years now but it feels like I’ve been here for a lot longer. It’s honestly hard to even think about what my life was like before I moved out here; I’ve done a lot of changing and growing in that time, and I’ve made tons of great friends as well.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor gazes dreamily in the direction of the espresso machine as he says the last part in particular, before giving his head a quick shake and returning to the conversation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“But, yeah, this place is pretty dang cool. There’s almost always something happening on any given day to suit anyone’s interests. What kinda stuff do you get up to, normally?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I shrug my shoulders. “Ah geez, I don’t know. I mean, I guess whatever people normally do? I like live music and I’m willing to bet there’s probably a fair amount of it that happens around here, any suggestions on that front?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor’s eyes light up. “Yes, actually! There’s a free show happening tonight at Big Tree, it doesn’t have any official advertising but here, lemme write down the time and address for you.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor’s enthusiasm visibly swells as he pulls out a pen and pad of paper from his bag. “I don’t know what you’re exactly in the mood for but you’ll probably get it with Constance. She’s so good at making chill, ambient vibes and then mixing it up so you can really get down and dance, too!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He rips the paper off the pad and shoves it into my hand before his eyes widen in excitement as a thought strikes him. “Do you want to go with me? Like, just as friends, no pressure there obviously, but do you wanna go together? I was thinking of getting some friends on board and we could all meet up and go as a group!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This unexpected burst of energy and sudden pressure to commit is a bit much for me to process all at once, and it takes several seconds before I think of something to say. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;However, before I even manage to get any words at all out, a large yellow coffee mug filled right up to the brim with a leaf shape set in the foam is placed directly in front of me. My eyes dart upward to see that looking down at both me and Trevor, once again having materialized seemingly out of nowhere, is a marginally annoyed Junip.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Here’s your coffee, dear,” he says with just the faintest tinge of snippiness in his voice. “I sure hope you weren’t planning on stealing this boy from me tonight, especially after I was so generous and welcoming to you just a bit ago.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My eyes flit back and forth between Junip, Trevor, and the extremely prominent bulge in Junip’s bike shorts which is now firmly at eye level with me. Trevor is blushing furiously and seems incapable of words, and is also firmly fixated on Junip’s crotch. I look back up at Junip and shake my head slightly yet definitively. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Lovely!” Junip says with a smile, all traces of annoyance having evaporated, before turning his attention to Trevor. “And as for &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;you…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This comment finally draws Trevor’s gaze away from Junip’s crotch and directly into his eyes in a flash, as if Junip had uttered a trigger phrase or something. “Are you forgetting that we had plans for tonight, hun?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor’s face turns a brilliant shade of beet red. “I… we… I mean…” He barely manages to choke out even that much before he loses focus and his eyes drift off to the side. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Junip rolls his eyes as he caresses Trevor’s cheek gently, nudging their gaze back towards his. ”Hey there sweetie, did you forget?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor breathes heavily at the sudden physical touch and gently commanding tone that Junip affects, before collecting himself and staring into Junip’s eyes with a tender and slightly apologetic look. “I… no, I didn’t forget, I just thought that we were gonna… y’know, do &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;that&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; after the show tonight?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This comment elicits a devious and sultry chuckle out of Junip. “Oh no hun, I’m coming over right after my shift and we’re getting straight to work. There won’t be time for anything else tonight, we’re going to be &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;quite &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;busy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor pouts slightly and opens his mouth to speak, but before they can say anything in protest Junip reaches his right hand out and hooks a finger around the loop attached to their choker, pulling him forward firmly and shutting him up in a heartbeat. Junip leans in closer until the two of them are mere inches apart.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You do still want me to train you, don’t you sweetie?” Junip keeps his voice only barely above a whisper. “I remember how desperate you were the last time to get as much practice in as possible. Do you remember?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor, who at this point looks as though they’re going to melt straight out of their clothes, nods their head vigorously as they affect a dopey grin.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What’s that?” Junip cocks his head to the side in mock confusion. “I don’t think I heard you, sweetie. Why don’t you try using your words?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor opens his mouth but pauses, his gaze drifting over towards me and his face suddenly flushing a dark red as he remembers he has an audience. The thought doesn’t last long, however, as Junip takes a finger on his free hand and presses it under Trevor’s chin, guiding his gaze back towards him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Go on dear, I’m waiting. And no rush, I’ve got all the time in the world for you, babe.” Junip’s expression visibly softens as he says that last part.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor’s mouth opens and closes noiselessly for several seconds before the words finally leave his throat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yes, Junip.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Junip’s free hand clasps Trevor by the chin. “Yes Junip, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;what?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor gulps, but then a deeply depraved expression crosses his face and his remaining inhibitions vanish as he firmly locks eyes with Junip. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yes, Junip, I want you to train me. Please.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A devious smile spreads across Junip’s mouth and he bites his bottom lip seductively as Trevor’s tongue caresses their own lips and their eyes fill with wanton desire. Junip’s smile warms decisively as he leans in to give Trevor a quick peck on their nose and lets go of both their chin and choker. “That’s my good demiboy,” Junip says as he ruffles Trevor’s hair before turning his attention to me, fully back to his cheerful and innocent self.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Enjoy your coffee hun!” Junip turns on his heel and heads back behind the counter, his tail barely missing hitting me in the face as it swings around but plapping against Trevor’s in the process. I watch him as he makes his way behind the counter and clicks his tongue and shoots a finger gun at Casper who looks deeply annoyed and embarrassed, seemingly to the point of wishing he could vanish from existence. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So… you two know each other, I take it?” I turn back towards Trevor as I say this, only to see him burying his face in his hands and breathing heavily. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I shift nervously in my seat, uncertain where to go from here. I look around and notice a couple newly empty tables.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Um, Trev?” I say trepidatiously. “Do you want me to… I don’t know, give you some space or someth…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“NOPE!! SORRY!! I’M GOOD!!” Trevor says more than a bit too loudly as he suddenly bolts upward and shakes himself vigorously. I wince as I look at the booth behind him; its occupants, an African wild dog wearing all black and a fox with white, orange, and black fur, have stopped dead in the middle of their conversation and are staring in our direction. I offer them both an embarrassed smile before Trevor pulls himself together with a deep and reverberating breath, staring at me with a profoundly embarrassed and apologetic expression.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh my goodness, Paige, I’m &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;so&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; sorry about all of that! I don’t think I’ve ever experienced anything quite like it before to be honest, and certainly not in front of someone I just met either! I don’t know what’s gotten into that boy today, but I hope that didn’t upset you any!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I stare back at them with my mouth slightly agog for several moments before my brain starts working again. “You’re good, no worries,” I say with a decidedly nervous chuckle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor takes a deep sigh and relaxes significantly. “Okay, whew! Junip can be pretty forward sometimes with his public displays of affection towards me but that was certainly a cut above what even I’m used to.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor takes another breath before finally regaining his composure. “So, yeah, I guess I won’t be at Constance’s show tonight but you should totally go! Lots of great peeps show up to her sets if you’re looking to socialize.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Uncertain of what to say further, I remember I have a coffee drink sitting in front of me so I grab it and take a larger than intended swig. The sudden and intense rush of flavor drives any remaining awkwardness or secondhand embarrassment out of my mind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, shit,” I say with a renewed vigor, “This is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;really &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;good!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor claps his hands together enthusiastically. “Yayyyy! I’m so happy I got to be here for your first order at The Nest! What did you get?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I take another deep drink from my mug, relishing in its deepness and complexity. “I got the daily special, figured it’s keeping with the theme of being more adventurous than normal today.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor squees loudly. “AAAAAHHH you got the rosemary and mint mocha?! I came up with that!!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I cock a confused eyebrow. “What? But Junip said that he…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor shakes his head and waves his hand dismissively. “Nahh, he got that from me! He gets a lot of his specials from me, frankly. Don’t tell him I told you though, I like letting him feel proud about it for the other customers.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I chuckle, the relationship between these two starting to make a bit more sense. “That’s big of you, I guess. Do you work here too?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He shakes his head. “Nah, I’ve got another job, and coffee’s really only a hobby of mine anyways. Also, this place is a co-op so whenever they do post a new job the competition is pretty stiff. Not that I don’t think I’d stand a chance but I’m happy where I’m at.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I chuckle again. “Well, if you ever changed your tune there I guess you’d have at least one person on staff who’d vouch for you.” I glance back towards the kitchen where Junip is engaged in a very one-sided conversation with Casper, who is fixated on Junip’s crotch and blushing furiously.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeeaaahhh…” Trevor looks back at Junip and smiles dopily, before turning back to me. “So what about you? Have you found a job yet?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I shake my head. “Nah, not yet, figured I’d live off my U.B.I. for a bit before pounding the pavement, but I’ve given some thought to…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Trevor and I chat for a bit longer about our work history, which despite not having much overlap we're still able to find common ground and share relatable stories about, before his alarm rings and he heads off to go run some errands. We exchange numbers before he does and promise to keep in touch, and as he leaves I feel much happier than at any point since my arrival. Not only have I made at least one friend but I did so by ignoring my anxiety and throwing caution to the wind, which gives me pause to consider how many times I’ve been dissuaded from that impulse in the past.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Checking the time on my phone shows that I have about a half hour before my registration interview at the gym, so I gather up my things and bring my dirty dishes to the bus tub before turning to head out the door, my nose buried in my phone as I attempt to pull up the map again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It’s at this point that I slam into what feels like a brick wall, dropping my phone to the floor and seeing another one tumble down and land next to it. Realizing what I’ve done I hurriedly drop to my knees to retrieve them, a hot wash of shame rising in my cheeks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh my god, I’m so sorry!” I sputter out my apology as I scramble to pick up both of them before looking upward. “I didn’t mean to…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;All of my thoughts are driven straight out of my head the second my eyes make contact with hers. Staring down at me is a tall and unbelievably beautiful cheetah woman with a mullet and the most well-defined six-pack abs I’ve ever seen in my life, wearing a white sports bra, black fingerless gloves, and maroon yoga pants, and holding a small to-go cup. She has a penetrating but concerned expression on her face as she looks me directly in the eyes, mine drifting downward as the intensity of her gaze finally becomes too much for me to handle. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I realize far too late what a mistake this is as it means I’m now staring straight into her crotch, and am now face to face with the incredibly unmistakable bulge resting there as well. I gulp, struggling to avert my gaze, when something else catches my attention. A potent and musky scent, unmistakable in its origin, invades my nostrils and floods my senses. My brain quickly shuts down everything but its basic motor functions as this intoxicating aroma penetrates its deepest recesses. My eyes shut in rapture, and without thinking I moan softly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Through the haze of this fog encompassing my brain, I hear a soft and somewhat evil chuckle. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uh, you doing okay down there, hun?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Reality crashes back in an instant as soon as I hear her speak and my eyes shoot open and back up to hers. She’s staring down at me and grinning with devious intent. I can feel my cheeks flushing in supreme embarrassment yet again and I fix my gaze firmly to the floor, breathing deliberately through my mouth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I… I… dah… uhhh…” I wrench my eyes shut as I hold her phone up in my right hand. “You dropped this.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I hear her chuckle again, this time tinged with a low growl, and I suddenly feel a strong hand grasp my wrist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, how clumsy of me.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Before I can even register what’s happening I feel her yank and pull me up onto my feet by my arm as easily as if I were a bag of feathers. By the time I open my eyes I’m already standing again, albeit a bit unsteadily, and I’m face to face with her chest. I slowly turn my gaze upward until her eyes are finally staring deep into mine once again. She fixes me with another grin as she lets go of my wrist and plucks her phone from my hand, all without taking her eyes off of mine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thank you, dear. How nice of you to help me like that.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I’m still completely speechless so all I can do is return her stare, my heart pounding like a kettle drum the entire time. Her dark brown eyes threaten to overtake my vision entirely and swallow me whole, and I can still smell the musky scent of her sweat as it pervades my senses. My mouth stammers open and shut as I attempt to pull myself together long enough to say even a single word, but nothing comes out. My flustered state is all too obvious, as she continues to grin before extending a hand in my direction.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s lovely to meet you, my name is Aster.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Seeing her hand in front of me fires a neuron in my brain and I reach out to grab it with my own, still straining to say anything at all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster chuckles. “Do &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; have a name, hun?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The question finally spurs my brain into a higher form of action. “PAIGE,” I say a tad loudly before catching myself. “My name is Paige and it’s… uh… it’s…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The words catch in my throat again as I see Aster smiling warmly, with only a touch of the deviousness from before. “Ooh, ‘Paige’. Such a lovely name for such a lovely girl.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I feel the hot blush in my cheeks rising yet again, and my eyes drift away from hers as an embarrassed smile betrays my emotions. “Oh, gee… thanks.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I realize I’m still shaking her hand and let go of it hurriedly, turning back to look at her again. “Umm, sorry about running into you like that, I wasn’t looking and, well, yeah…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster clucks her tongue as she gives me a small dismissive wave. “Oh, water under the dam, sweetie. These things happen, and frankly I’d probably only have been annoyed if I’d dropped my doppio.” She holds up her to-go cup to indicate it with a small wink, which manages to get a giggle out of me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well I’m glad it wasn’t that disastrous,” I say, my brain deciding to finally start working again. “I’d have been out a whole two dollars to replace it for you if it was.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster grins again as she cocks an eyebrow at me. “Ooh, cute &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; courteous, a double threat I see.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My cheeks threaten to burn straight off of my face as I feel the blood rush into them and my heart rate quickens. The struggle to maintain my composure is all too obvious, given Aster’s amused yet subtly triumphant reaction. “I call them as I see them hun, and you seem like a real sweetheart.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I can’t help but giggle again. “Gosh, are you &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;trying&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; to get me to fall to pieces?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She grins even wider and her eyes drift off to the side coyly. “Mmmaybe…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I grin, my confidence finally starting to bolster. “Well, it seems like we were both on our way out. May I escort you to the door?” I hold my hand out to her in a dainty display of mock chivalry. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her expression softens a touch as she reaches down to accept my hand. “Why thank you my dear, let us away from this place, I grow weary of it and require a change of scenery.” The faux-Victorian tone she affects is so sudden and seemingly out of character for her that I can’t help but giggle and blush more, which causes her to smile warmly and give my hand a tiny squeeze.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, beat it you two, you’re making me sick.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We both turn our heads towards the source of the interruption and see Junip, leaning across the counter and resting his head in his hands as he fixes us with an intolerably smug grin. I furrow my brow in annoyance and I feel Aster squeeze my hand even harder as a low growl escapes her throat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You better watch yourself, boy. Keep that up and I’ll beat your ass into the ground during our next session.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Junip’s grin somehow grows even wider and his tail flits back and forth seductively. “Oooh, is that a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;promise&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I hear Aster inhale sharply and her hand threatens to crush mine. “Don’t say I didn’t warn you, you little shit.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Turning back to me Aster notices my pained expression and quickly lets go of my hand, offering up an embarrassed smile as compensation. Junip gives a cheeky wave as we turn away and head for the door, while Casper shoots him a look that could curl the paint off a wall.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster turns to me as we step outside and head for the sidewalk. “So, what direction are you headed in?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I take a moment to confirm my location and the general area. “Uhh, to the right I think. That’s where I was going before the smell of coffee distracted me and I’ve got an intake appointment with Valley Fitness in about 25 minutes.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster’s eyes widen and her smile grows to match. “You don’t say? I’m headed there myself!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I feel my heart increasing in pace again and bite my lip in a mostly successful attempt at keeping my emotions in check. “Hah, small world! Although…” I take a moment to stare pointedly at her abs before giving her a cheeky grin. “I can’t say it’s much of a shock to hear that. I bet a physique like that takes a lot of work to maintain.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster chuckles again. “Oh, it’s not as much work as you might think. It’s more about maintaining a baseline at this point, which involves eating healthy and doing at least a few reps every day. I only hit the gym about three to four times a week so it’s not like I live there or anything.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It’s my turn to laugh, and I don’t even bother to hide the incredulity in it. “Wow, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;only&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; three to four times? What do you do the other half of the week, spend it preparing to work out or something?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She cocks an eyebrow and grins at me again, reaching an arm around my shoulder to give it just a tiny squeeze. “Stick around long enough and I’ll show you.” She shoots me a wink as she talks, and my composure starts to crack yet again as I feel a bead of sweat forming on my brow and I bite my lip even harder. I look up into Aster’s eyes and I feel the warmth rising in my cheeks yet again, my own eyes trembling in anticipation, as she stares down at me with clear, devious intent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“ASTER!! YO, ASTER!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Mercifully, the moment is broken by a voice crying out from up the sidewalk and before either of us can fully register it Aster is being glomped by a squealing mass of light brown fur with freckles and a turquoise fringe. It takes a couple seconds for me to process that the mass is actually a short and chubby Shiba Inu who is wearing a gray t-shirt, red shorts, and has a rather overstuffed backpack slung over her shoulders. Once that same processing hits Aster her face brightens up in an instant and she hugs her back.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Beruca!” Aster cries out warmly. “I haven’t seen you in a month, at least! What’ve you been up to, dear?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh goodness, soooo much!” Beruca brings her head up from Aster’s chest and stands on her tip-toes to give her a peck on the lips, which Aster returns in kind. “I was out of town for a while, taking some P.T.O. or whatever qualifies for that in my line of work, but I’ve also been busy on some new projects of mine too! We have to go out for drinks sometime soon and I can tell you all about them!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster smiles and nods her head. “Oh yes, that’d be lovely! I’m free this Sunday, if that works for you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s a date!” Beruca turns towards me and her joyful and innocent smile quickly shifts to an evil grin that seems more befitting of her. “And who, may I ask, is this lovely lady you seem to have taken under your wing? Another, *ahem*, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;student&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; of yours?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Beruca’s deliberate choice of words causes Aster to hurriedly remove her arm from around my shoulders, as well as myself to continue blushing even harder. All of this only pushes Beruca’s grin even wider across her face and elicits a devious chuckle out of her in the process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Beruca, this is Paige, and we’ve only just recently made each other’s acquaintance. As in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;less than five minutes ago&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; acquainted.” Aster makes no effort to hide the emphasis on her words, which has zero effect on Beruca’s disposition or her grin.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“As if that’s ever stopped anyone from… well, making a long-lasting and deeply affecting &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;personal connection&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; with someone.” Beruca rolls her eyes in a display of mock coyness. “After all, it’s not as if I have any experience in that realm, or know anyone else who does.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Before Aster can say anything else Beruca gives her another hug. “Ahh you know I’m just jerkin’ you around, right hun?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aster sighs and returns the hug with a soft chuckle. “Yeah, I know. I can never stay mad at you anyways, and it’s good to see you again babe.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yay!” Beruca breaks away and looks back up at her. “Well, I’d love to stay and chat some more but I really gotta make this delivery before Casper loses his mind, he’s been blowing my phone up for the last hour. See you soon!” She turns to me and shoots that devious grin in my direction again. “And I hope to be seeing more of you too, Paige. Although, I must say I doubt that hope will go unsatisfied.” She gives me a quick wink and pat on the shoulder as she breezes past us and towards The Nest.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I turn back to look up at Aster, who is still looking at Beruca as she leaves. “So… she seems… uh…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The words catch in my throat again once Aster stares back at me. “Oh, don’t worry about Beruca, dear. She’s quite upfront and doesn’t have much of a filter on her but she’s also a real sweetie. I love her, and I hope you get a chance to spend some quality time with her too.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I nod, finding my voice again. “Yeah, I could tell. She did seem nice, pretty intimidating though. Although I’d be lying if I said that wasn’t the general vibe of today for me. Everything and everyone has been so lovely and nice, but it’s also been kinda scary too.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I realize too late the implications of saying that to Aster and I feel the blood rush to my face again. “Umm, that is, I-I didn’t mean that…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She chuckles warmly and places a hand on my shoulder, shutting me up in record time. “Oh don’t worry sweetie, I get it. A lot of people are intimidated by me, even if they’ve known me for a while. I can’t say I blame them, because it’s not exactly like I don’t want to present an image of strength and power, but I do like giving people a chance to get to know me all the same.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her eyes drift away from mine for a moment and, astonishingly, I see a small tinge of red creep into her cheeks. “So,” she says with clear embarrassment, “With that in mind, I’d like to help you feel welcome here. If you wanted to, I’d love to accompany you with whatever you do today. Maybe we can get to know each other better, and you won’t feel quite so scared?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I smile, a small lump rising in my throat, as I witness this clearly uncharacteristic display of vulnerability from Aster. Without thinking, I wrap my arm around her waist and give her a small squeeze. She takes in a slight but sharp inhale as I do and her smile warms to match mine, her hand moving across to my other shoulder and squeezing me in gently. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I think that would be lovely, Aster. Thank you so much for being so generous.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her smile takes on a decidedly more devious bent as she holds me closer, the muscles of her arm tensing and pressing into the back of my neck, and my heart increasing in its pace once more.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, I can’t wait to show you just how generous I can be, my dear.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Flustered, I turn away from her gaze again and giggle softly, which causes that evil chuckle to find its way back out of her throat. She holds out her other hand to indicate the path in front of us and we start down it again. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;TO BE CONTINUED&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
