      <title>How it&amp;#8217;s done</title>
      <author> TernUnfettered </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1249595/how-its-done/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1249595-how-its-done/chapter/1249606/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">e53fd4187d97197dc35a0eed24a4a01399cd6d97</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tired of witnessing and hearing about his lifelong friend's failed relationships with men and her horrendous flirting game, Riley realizes that he needs to show her how it's done.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1249595-how-its-done/chapter/1249606/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;How it’s done&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I just thought I’d finally found the one.” Amy sighed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley rolled his eyes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s weird. I thought it was all perfect. He was sweet, attractive.” She went on, “A lot of girls would love to have a guy like him, I just don’t know what went wrong.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley groaned in response.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What?” Amy questioned. “Is something bothering you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What do you think?” Riley asked in a sarcastic tone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Literally everything about this conversation. Here they were, old high school friends having their bi-monthly cup of coffee together at a local cafe to catch up and talk about their lives, only for Amy to reveal that her latest relationship hadn’t worked out. It frustrated him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Umm, I’m not sure.” Amy answered. “Sorry, am I being too negative?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s not that,” Riley sighed. “It’s just…! Like jesus girl, I’m sorry but I’m not even surprised.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wait, about my breakup?!” Amy gasped. “How could you say that?!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ames, I’ve known you for over a decade,” Riley looked directly into her eyes, a serious expression. “And in that entire time, you have never known how to flirt.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That’s not true!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Remember Randy Kelly? I was dying from second-hand embarrassment when I had to watch that.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That was junior year! God!” Amy countered. “That was years ago, we’re adults now! I just finished college for crying out loud! I know how to flirt with a guy!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Okay, then prove it.” Riley leaned back on his chair, arms crossed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Huh?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Try to flirt with me.” He gestured at her. “Come on, just try.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Umm…” She seemed visibly nervous at the suggestion. “Y-You can’t just put me on the spot-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Prove it.” Riley repeated.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After a short nervous silence, Amy straightened her back and pushed her awkwardness behind a small smile. “H-Hey there handsome, what are you gonna do tonight?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Nil. Zero points.” Riley hit back. “You fail.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I only just started!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah and you failed miserably.” Riley shook his head. “I mean come on, where do I even start?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy pushed a hand onto the table. “Like you would even know! You’re a straight guy, who hasn’t ever even had an actual girlfriend himself!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That just makes it more embarrassing,” Riley argued back. “Imagine, a straight guy knows more than a girl about this stuff. It’s pathetic.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’re just saying that because you can’t prove it! You have no idea how hard it is to-!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley suddenly stood up.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wait- huh? Are you leaving already?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Nope.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Then what are you-?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m gonna show you how it’s done.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;All Riley had said after that was for Amy to meet him at the local nightclub later that night. Needless to say, she was very confused at the suggestion, though she wouldn’t mind it if this was his way of helping. The two had trouble fitting in back in high school, so they had a habit of having each other’s backs. Maybe he was going to help her find a rebound once he got there, that’d be nice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But that’d assuming he wasn’t standing her up for some reason. Seriously, where was-?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A light voice mimicked a cough behind her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy turned to see a beautiful woman looking at her. Long golden hair framing a delicate face, decorated with the type of eye-catching makeup you usually saw at nightclubs. Red lipstick, dark eyeshadow, even some hoop earrings. Her red dress was plenty eye-catching on its own, form-fitting but in a slight and subtle way. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“O-Oh I’m sorry, did you need something-?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s me, Ames.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy blinked. Wait, her voice was a tad husky… And that face, come to think of it…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wait, Riley?!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What? Did you think I was somebody else?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“W-Well, yeah! I’ve never seen you like this, you’re… beautiful?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley let out a short giggle, “Well thanks, glad the effort paid off.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wait, so is this you coming out to me or something?” Amy asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What? No. Remember what we talked about earlier today? This is for the bet.” Riley answered like it was obvious.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Huh? The thing about my flirting? You bought a dress and got yourself dolled up like a woman would so you could help me with guys? And are you wearing breast forms under there? When or where would you even buy that?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley scrunched up his face, “Why would I buy those? I already had everything in my closet for emergencies.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Emergencies?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, when stuff like this happens.” Riley gestured to himself, then looked over at a group of men chatting. “Oh, hey, those guys look decent. Watch, I’m gonna show you how it’s done.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“But wait, I don’t-!” But before Amy could stop her, Riley was off strutting to the other end of the club. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She was a bit too nervous to follow behind, but she saw how things proceeded. Riley started talking to one of the men, who clearly assumed he was a woman, and soon they were flirting up a storm. Riley kept lightly touching the man’s arms, and they both smiled widely as they talked. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy couldn’t be too caught up in the details of what they were doing or saying, as her mind just kept wandering to what the hell her friend was thinking. Not just that, but that he seemed so adept at this. When she thought back to her own experiences, she’d always been so clumsy. Amy could hardly believe it, he was straight up better at this than her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And the two were only drawn closer together as their conversation passed. The guy was clearly separated from his original group, far more preoccupied with the beautiful girl in front of him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What happened next Amy couldn’t even believe. Riley seemed to nod, biting his lip, and the next thing she knew the guy was cupping his chin and kissing him. She gaped.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It only lasted for a few seconds, they weren’t getting frisky or anything. But once it was over Riley slipped a note to the guy, before strutting back on over to Amy, waving a flirty little wave back to him in the process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy wasn’t sure what to even say to all of that.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“See? I’m pretty sure he was looking at my butt too when I walked away. I was flawless there.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy just looked back at Riley in disbelief. “Y-You really…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yep. It was &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;so &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;easy. Men are putty in your hands if you just smile and say or do the right things. Even &lt;em&gt;I &lt;/em&gt;know this. He even asked to kiss me, and who was I to say no?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I-I mean you didn’t have to.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That’s what you do when you hit it off so well at a nightclub. It’s okay to get a bit intimate. Also it leaves him wanting for more, hence why I gave him my number.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“B-But still!” Amy rebuked. “That’s just picking guys up! Flirting with a guy and giving his number is totally different from actually dating!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley was about to object, but instead cupped his chin. “Hmm, good point…” But then he brushed it all off. “Well, I guess we’ll see about that.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;There was an awkward silence as Riley took a sip from his drink, while Amy continued to process the situation in her head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...So you don’t wanna give it a go yourself?” Riley finally asked. “His friends are also pretty good-looking, maybe you can give one of them your number.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“N-No thanks, I’m good.” Amy silently groaned. Safe to say, she did not feel in the mood to make any pass on a guy herself tonight.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy squinted her eyes as she tried to make sense of the pic Riley was showing her on his phone. It was a girl snuggled up in a guy’s arms, smiling widely as she looked up at him kissing her on the forehead, while he held the camera to take the picture. It was some cheesy couples pic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So that’s…?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yep, me and Mark.” Riley answered with a nod.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy squinted further. That was definitely Riley alright, albeit dressed up as a girl again like that time at the nightclub. This time it was a whole different outfit though. More casual autumn-wear that was cute in a homely way, instead of the nightclub attire meant to draw eyes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So you really pulled it off, huh…” Amy wasn’t sure how to feel about this. Riley had already proven his point two months ago, but apparently he wanted to drive it home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yep. We’re two months strong now.” He put his phone back into his pocket. “It really is that easy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy had no counterargument. The times she actually had a boyfriend, they never lasted longer than two months. But even if she did, she wouldn’t even &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;want&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; to argue. Riley had already gone way past his original point, and at this stage there was no reason to encourage him to rub it in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well, I’m happy for you, I guess…” Amy sipped from her drink. “So what are you gonna do now? Break up with him?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Y-Yeah, I guess that’s what has to happen next now…” Riley sighed, almost in a way where he was letting out some hidden frustration.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Surprised he hasn’t found out already.” Amy pointed out. “Like I get it, you look good in that pic, but all the guys I knew were pretty aggressive about sex.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, he’s oddly sweet like that. He hasn’t been forceful or anything.” Riley nodded. “...It’s so weird when I think about it. It’s like he lights up whichever room he’s in, just makes everything all better.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uh-huh.” Amy leaned on her arm as she stirred her drink, bored.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m gonna feel mean when I have to do it, but I have a plan to let him down easy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And what’s that?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m going to tell him that I’m transgender.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy blinked, straightening her back up. “What?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s the perfect excuse.” Riley argued. “After all, that’s what it would look like. I could even take off my disguise or show him my penis if he doesn’t believe me.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Y-You don’t need to go that far with the last part!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I mean just hypothetically. I’m saying it’s the most consistent reason I could give him considering my actual body. And since most guys don’t like to date trans girls, we’ll just settle our differences and part ways.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy felt unsure. “Don’t guys freak out about stuff like that though? Like make sure you’re being safe about it.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh no, I will.” Riley reassured. “Besides, Mark is such a gentleman that I’m sure he’ll be relaxed about it. We’ll end things amicably, and we never have to worry about each other again.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy nodded, “Well alright, if you say so. Just hope it goes well.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What about you? Still haven’t given anybody a shot?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy sighed. “I dunno, I think I’m just exhausted with that whole game.” It would probably be weird to say that Riley’s actions had been discouraging her. “But time will tell.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“........Riley.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley stopped checking his makeup, “Yes?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...Is there something you need to tell me?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He awkwardly shuffled in his seat, “N-Not particularly, no...”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Is there a reason you’re dressed as a woman, right now?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...W-Well, I was going to have a date with Mark after this, so I figured it’d be more convenient if… well…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy had been baffled when meeting up with Riley again, expecting him in his usual male getup, only to reencounter the beautiful girl version of him. A date too, of course it’s a date. He’s coordinated a cute outfit that matches him perfectly, he’s only gotten better with his looks and fashion. Everything about his gestures and mannerisms were also remarkably more feminine. Just how much further has he taken this?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Ultimately, she sighed. “So I take it you didn’t break up.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley shied his gaze away.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...What happened?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well, I tried what I said I’d do… We met up in public, and I told him that we couldn’t keep dating because I was trans a-and…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“No way...”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“He didn’t care!” Riley answered in a panic. “He said he loved me anyway and that my past didn’t matter to him! A-And I just couldn’t say no! I’ve told you how he is!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...That he’s incredibly sweet? That he lights up every room he’s in and makes everything better?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Exactly!” Riley responded, almost exasperated. “He was even nice enough to help me schedule an appointment for hormone replacement theory. I-It’s not like I wanted it, but I figured it may as well help me with my story in the meanwhile…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So you guys are just dating for real now?” Amy asked. It was difficult to imagine how Riley would have to deal with this.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well kinda. I think I might have to update my facebook soon. Y-You know, for consistency. Maybe I just keep pretending to be a trans girl to the rest of the world?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Why can’t you just break up with him for some other normal reason?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I can’t do that!” Riley pushed his hand on the table. “Have you seen how he smiles?! How could anyone say no to that?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And oh my gosh his eyes.” Riley continued. “I swear it’s like they have a hypnotic effect, sometimes he practically stuns me into silence when he looks at me the right way. And don’t even get me started on his arms. He goes to the gym, and you can &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;tell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;. It’s hard &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;not&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; to find excuses to cling onto him when we’re on a date.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He smiled dreamily, lifting a hand to try and cover his mouth. “And even if that’s not enough, he keeps finding a way to be the absolute sweetest. He knows just how to treat a girl. A-And I know I’m not actually one but ever since I said I was a trans girl and that it made me insecure when trying to break up he’s only been even more precious with me and I just…! He’s literally so perfect, and-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Okay, that’s enough.” Amy did not need to hear any more. She’s gotten long tired of any and all relationship talk. She hadn’t even bothered thinking about guys or dating in the months since their last conversation. Her interest was completely dead. “I get it, you’re a happy couple now.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“N-No, not actually.” Riley tries to refute. “I’m still thinking of a way to end things. It’s just hard because-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s hard because he’s hot?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well I wouldn’t say &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;that&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;.” Riley answered. “I mean, I’m still not gay.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy didn’t answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I just don’t want to let him down,” He continued with a sigh. “I’m worried I’d break his heart, and that would just make me feel worse and more miserable about it…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uh-huh,” Amy nodded. Somehow, the more they talked about this the weirder she felt. “But everything else is going well?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh! Oh yeah, for sure.” Riley nodded affirmatively. “Honestly if it was a real relationship it’d be really good. Since we’re both kinda fresh out of college with debt he’s been talking about moving in together next year. And despite faking everything it still feels &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;really&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; good to kiss him, which feels crazy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Funny how that happens.” Amy leaned forward with her chin on her palm.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know, right? I guess he’s just &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;that&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; good at it.” Riley nodded, taking a sip from his drink.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Suddenly a man approached from behind, lightly touching Riley’s shoulders. “Boo!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ah!” Riley yelped as she shook, looking behind her. “Oh thank god, you scared me Mark! I almost spilled my drink!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh whoops! Sorry, sorry,” Mark grinned, “I just saw my favorite person and wanted to say hi.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Jeez, the date’s not even for almost another hour.” Riley argued back, his face flushing a light shade of red.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know, but I wanted to head out early on a walk, get a little something for the occasion. And then I noticed you!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley let out a short giggle, “Well I &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;am&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; glad to see you too…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley had a wistful, goofy and dreamlike smile as Mark leaned in and wrapped an arm around him. The situation was worse than Amy thought, Riley really did look almost spellbound there judging by her expression.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, and is this your friend?” Mark asked, turning to Amy and leaning over to offer his hand. “Hi, I’m Mark, Riley’s boyfriend.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy shook it, “I’ve heard a lot about you.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“U-Umm-uhh, eheh…” Riley seemed like he could barely get a word out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Mark let go of his girlfriend and stood back up. “It’s nice meeting you. But uh I don’t want to bother you two. I’ll just catch you on the date later, Riley!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley was about to wave and bid farewell when Amy interrupted, “Actually, it’s fine. I was thinking of heading home a bit early anyway. You two can go have fun.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley looked back at Amy unsure, to which Amy winked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She lay a gentle hand on her friend’s shoulder. “Good luck!” She whispered. Whether that was for her goal to eventually break up with him, or with the relationship in general, Amy wasn’t sure. But it would feel wrong if she didn’t offer her friend her blessings either way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy took another bite out of the wedding cake. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The ceremony was over, so there wasn’t much left to do but enjoy the dinner and socialize. Well, at least try to. She was a bridesmaid, but it had been hard to get a word in with the bride with so many guests talking to the happy couple. Amy felt bad, as scheduling conflicts prevented her from attending the bachelorette party, so she hadn’t much been able to talk to her at all. It figured. Even her own plus one had gone to the bathroom and was taking a while, so that left her pretty alone at the moment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hey!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy looked up, “Oh hey! If it isn’t the lucky bride herself!” She stood up, offering her lifelong friend a hug.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley looked back at Amy, using a small napkin to wipe a quick tear from her eye. “I’m so glad you came! I’m sorry you couldn’t make it to the party!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy shook her head, offering a reassuring smile. “It’s okay, it happens. So long as I was able to make it to your big day. How’s Mark doing?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The two sat down together. “Oh he’s having fun. He has a lot of relatives though, so getting to talk to everyone has been really tiring for him.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy nodded, “I can imagine.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Honestly I still can’t get over his suit.” Riley added. “I know that the bride’s the one you’re supposed to hide from the groom for good luck, but ugh he cleaned up so goooood!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“He also looked really happy to see you.” Amy pointed out. “I mean, come on, they had to have spent hours on your makeup, right? You’re gorgeous!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Aw, thanks.” Riley flushed a bit. “Honestly, I’ve been looking forward to the altar for so long. I know it’s cliché, but this is definitely the happiest day of my life.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy smiled to her friend, “I’m really glad to hear that.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The two continued sitting there, silent. It was awkward to be sure, which made sense. They hadn’t been able to stay in touch for long, both getting too busy with more life stuff. In some way, the wedding invitation had been an incredibly welcome surprise to reunite one more time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...And that, my friend, is how it’s done.” Riley suddenly said, smiling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Huh?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“How you flirt with men.” She explained. “See? Even a straight guy could do it.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’re still saying that?” Amy asked. “I don’t know about you, but I don’t think Mark just married a straight guy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“U-Umm no yeah, that’s uhh…” Riley hesitated. “Y-Yeah, safe to say I’m probably not actually a guy at all.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Took you this long?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It was actually when he proposed. It got hard to deny after that point.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That’s still way too long.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ahem,” Riley regained her composure, “But I was a straight guy when I made the bet, so technically it still counts. I totally won and completely destroyed you. I even got married!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy rolled her eyes, but she had trouble hiding her smirk. “Yeah, whatever.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m just saying,” She continued. “It’s still ironic to me. You’d think a cis girl would have had more experience than me and had it easier.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Riley,” Amy looked her dead in the eye. “I’m a lesbian.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Just then Jean came back from the bathroom, sitting down in her chair as she gave Amy a quick peck on the check. “Hey, babe.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley, almost frozen in shock, just let out an “oh.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Jean offered her hand, “Nice to meet you! And congratulations!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Riley nodded slowly as she shook her hand, thoughts running through her mind. “Huh.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Comphet’s a bitch.” Amy nodded to herself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wow, so this was all for nothing.” Riley sighed. “All this to show you how to flirt with a guy, and you don’t even like guys at all.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Amy shrugged, “I think the problem was always that guys just weren’t for me. It feels easier and more right for me when I flirt with other girls.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...” Riley didn’t say anything, leaning forward on the table and cupping her head in her hands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As Amy thought about it more, the whole thing only seemed sillier and more nonsensical the longer time went on, and it was already silly when it started. But at the very least, it seemed as if the bet had helped the both of them understand themselves in a deeper and better way than they ever had when they were younger.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Suddenly, Riley straightened back up and flashed a smug smirk. “Okay, but even then I still bet that I could flirt with girls better than you, even as a straight girl.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Riley, you’re married.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
