      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Elster has dreams aboard the Penrose-512. Sometimes, they are unpleasant, but most of the time, they are magical.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A gift fic for my friend Janet.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1248908-a-life-with-you/chapter/1248910/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Full Story&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alarms blared. Controls shook. Walls became hot to the touch.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;From her seat in the co-pilot’s chair, Elster pulled back on the control stick with all her might, bending the very metal of its construction in a desperate attempt to level the Penrose-512 out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Beside her, Ariane was glued to her seat. Her screams could not even be heard over the violent throttling their weary ship was undergoing as it burned through the atmosphere. Elster gritted her teeth hard enough to feel them threaten to come loose from all the vibrations cascading throughout the Penrose-512.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The glass on the altitude indicator cracked. Display screens sparked out. Cracks began to spread across the flight deck screen.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And all the while the garbled speakers continued to count down their impending demise.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Five-hundred meters.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The last of the CRT control displays went dark.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Four-hundred meters.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster began to scream as she summoned the last reserves of her strength.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Three-hundred meters.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane began to call her name, but her voice was entirely lost in the chaos.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Two-hundred meters.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The control stick ripped out from its fixture.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;One-hundred meters.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster dove to the other seat and used her body to cover as much of Ariane as she could.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;An explosion rocked as the ship impacted the ground.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster screamed as she rose from bed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She fell out of the bunk and onto her knees as her vision filled with countless error messages. She grasped at her throat, coughing, sputtering, unable to breathe, her vision starting to go dark.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane was by her side in an instant. She quickly grasped Elster’s shoulders and turned her to face her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ellie! Elster!” she called out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster’s eyes darted all over the room as she continued to hack and cough before eventually settling on Ariane’s.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ellie… just listen to me breathe, okay?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She weakly nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane slowly began to breathe in and breathe out very deliberately, trying to keep a steady and consistent tempo for Elster to try and match. Elster, for her part, eventually started out with quick, rapid, unfocused breaths, but the longer she looked at Ariane and watched her breath in and out, the more controlled her breathing became, slowly starting to lengthen out and adopt a more consistent rhythm. Ariane gradually increased her tempo, intending to meet Elster in the middle and bring her back down together, and as they got closer and closer, she gently grabbed Elster’s head and pulled it sideways against her chest.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Listen to my heartbeat, Ellie.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The combination of Ariane’s breathing and her heart’s naturally slowing beat as the adrenaline wore off had the final intended effect, and soon, she was able to fully match her breathing with Ariane’s. There, the two sat interlinked for several minutes, just breathing, just constantly reminding themselves of each other’s presence for as long as they wanted.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Then, Elster turned and threw her arms around Ariane, hugging her firmly as she hugged back. Silent, but with a whirlwind of emotions exchanged just from that simple touch.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It’s okay, Ellie… it’s over.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Soon, Elster sat on the side of the bed, cocooned in a thick, warm blanket as Ariane briefly left to fetch her some calming, herbal tea. She kept the memory of Ariane’s breathing right at the forefront of her thoughts, and every time that didn’t feel like enough, like her panic threatened to send her over the edge again, she heard Ariane’s voice faintly from the mess hall, reminding her that she wasn’t alone.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re going to be okay, Ellie.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ll be right back, Ellie.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re doing so well, Ellie.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her voice was hoarse as she thanked Ariane for the warm cup of chamomile tea. Being a Replika, it shouldn’t have mattered that she now had a warm, soothing beverage to help calm her nerves, but it worked anyway, and every light sip combined with every rub Ariane gave her shoulder as she sat next to her served to finally end that chaotic, all too unfortunate incident.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I am okay,” Elster eventually said aloud.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane nodded and reached over to kiss her cheek. “I knew you would be,” she claimed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster lightly smiled before she pulled one arm out from her cocoon of a blanket and used it to wrap the blanket around Ariane’s shoulders, sharing their body heat and linking them together even further. Ariane scooched up as close as she could to Elster, her thigh squishing against Elster’s polyethylene-coated appendage. She leaned her head against Elster’s shoulder and sighed peacefully as things finally seemed to have fully calmed down.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Only, the chaos left behind some doubt.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey, Ellie?” Ariane eventually and sheepishly asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster finished her sip of tea and exhaled softly before she replied. “Yes, what is it?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane sighed again as she reached over with her far hand and gently rubbed Elster’s leg. “Do you… like… sleeping in the same bed together?” she quietly asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster finished the last of her tea and set the mug to her side. She instantly saw through Ariane’s careful words and got to the exact point she was concerned about.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You are wondering if I prefer resting in my maintenance pod, since I only dream when I sleep naturally, and thus I would not have nightmares if I did not spend my nights here in your bed with you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane blinked a few times at Elster’s spot-on deduction, huffing with amusement at how much more socially adept her partner had become on their journey together. “Yeah… I… do worry about that,” she eventually admitted.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded and put her hand atop Ariane’s. Slowly, the two wiggled their fingers together so they were interlocked, and Elster lightly squeezed her partner’s hand before she leaned her head against the top of Ariane’s.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I would not trade what I have now for anything, Ariane.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane instantly smiled at Elster’s strong approval, turning her hand around so their palms faced each other for another light squeeze of the hands. However, her smile quickly faded somewhat, as this query would not fall from a single response.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“But…” Ariane paused briefly. She reached over with her other hand and grasped Elster’s forearm, lightly squeezing it as she continued speaking. “Your nightmares are so awful… I just… worry… about you…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I understand,” Elster replied. She leaned back from Ariane and gently pinched her chin, turning her head to meet her gaze, and so she could see the warm, genuine smile she put on for her sake. “But, you are always here to help me. So, while they may be unpleasant… I know I do not need to fear them,” she explained.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane sniffled and reached up to rub her eyes. “Ellie…” she muttered, sniffling again.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You gave me the courage to face this, just as you gave me the courage to accept persona degradation,” Elster continued to explain. She paused briefly to lean forward and surprise her partner with a peck on the lips. “Plus, I think the good outweighs the bad,” she added.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane raised an eyebrow at the same time she blushed from the kiss. “What do you mean, Ellie?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster widened her smile as she cocked her head forward. “Well, I have not relayed to you any of the good dreams I have experienced since I began sleeping with you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You remember them?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded. “All of them,” she said without hesitation. “Would you like to hear one?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane smiled warmly for Elster and nodded before she settled back to resting her head against her shoulder. They held each other's hands between them, tugging the ends of the blankets into a tighter wrap around themselves as Elster told the story of her dream.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;…..&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;We were in this grand, elaborate ballroom, similar to the one that appeared in that movie we watched about the revolution. An orchestra played live, gentle swing music, and everyone attending was finely dressed, I was wearing what I believe was called a ‘tuxedo’. Servers came around with trays full of champagner, and so many people were talking, laughing, and dancing. It was a party, but what for I was not interested in.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I was focused solely on you.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You approached me in a spectacular, sparkling, flowing, lavender dress with elbow-length silk gloves, and knee-high stockings, and with your beautiful hair tied into a loose bun. With tears in your eyes, you extended your hand to me, which I lightly grasped in my white-gloved hand before I tenderly kissed the tips of your fingers, also just like the movie we watched.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And, we danced.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Every step was perfect, and the busy ballroom around us faded away as we focused solely on each other, and the flow of the music. I spun you, dipped you, we swayed back and forth, laughing, crying tears of joy that we got to spend our time together like this, and when every song ended, we each pulled the other in to share a long and passionate kiss before they started the next tune.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;We returned to our home after a long night of dancing together. You told me a salacious joke at the door while you pulled off my bowtie and tossed it aside. Each of us undid pieces of each other’s clothing as we made our way to the bedroom, to the point where my jacket and waistcoat were off, and my shirt was unbuttoned down to my stomach, while you remained only in your sparkling dress.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You fell back onto our bed, your now loose hair spilling out around your head like the rays of the Vinetan sun. I climbed over you and descended to share in a passionate kiss. Your arms wrapped around me and you dug your fingers into the muscles on my back, trying to peel back the last garment covering my torso. Eventually, I leaned back onto my knees and pulled it off; unbuttoned my pants as well, but, for now, I was more focused on you. One hand I splayed across your stomach, feeling its smooth, concave contours and lines behind the skintight silk dress, and with my other hand I drew a line down your side from your chest to your gently curved hips, where I finally hooked my fingers under the hem of your dress and began to lift.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Do you need a moment, Ellie?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Hmm? No, I am alright… I was just… thinking about how to phrase this next part.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Alright, take your time, my love.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What remained underneath was already laden with your sweet nectar, the surest sign that in that moment, we needed each other more than anything else in the entire galaxy. I peeled your smallclothes away and dove into your snow-white orchard. You cried out my name endlessly, I bit, ate, lapped, and devoured your bounty. Your body squirmed with every flick of my tongue, thighs slapping, squeezing against my head, hands bunched up the bedsheets, pulling them from their tucked-in corners, head bounced back and forth as tension repeatedly built up and released far into the night.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I lost count of how many times I heard you say, “I love you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I finally moved once you began to tug on my hair. I knew what you wanted, and as you tried to catch your breath, I pulled off the last of my clothes. I walked on my knees along you until I reached your head, whereupon I gave you the tasting you desired so badly. I felt you inside me, pleasuring parts of me I never understood how much I ached for, making me feel sensations I did not think I was capable of feeling. I gripped the back of the bed frame hard to steady myself; too hard, in fact, as with one deft stroke of your tongue against me, I squeezed too hard and splintered the fine wood construction.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I could not speak, I could barely breathe. I only cried.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And I got voracious.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I needed to feel all of you against me, and I could not wait another moment; I tore apart your dress and picked you up. We squeezed our bodies hard against each other, your thin, delicate, but fierce physique against my strong, corded, but gentle one, each of us stealing the other’s air as we writhed about in bed, hands busy at work amidst each other’s pleasure. I grabbed one of your small, but agonizingly tender breasts and bit around your nipple, drawing all kinds of sounds and delicate sweetness from you as your fingers working within threatened to send me into a coma. You found the contours of my abdominal muscles and kissed and drew your tongue against nearly all of it, marveling at how every action sent a different cluster of muscles throughout my body into spasm. Tongues explored each other’s mouths, occasionally getting nibbled on, but eventually, breathing slowed, movements became gentle and tender, and shockwaves rolled out as calm crashes against the shoreline, rather than a cascade of titanic tsunamis. We lay in a spread of crumpled bedsheets, sweat, nectar, and a small amount of passionate, sanguine bliss from when our teeth and nails did too much of the talking.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I felt the last of my strength fade from sheer exhaustion, but not fast enough to forgo sharing one last kiss, and one last declaration of our enduring love for each other.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I love you, Ariane.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“And I love you too, Elster.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;….&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane sniffled briefly as she rubbed the heartfelt tears from her eyes. “Do you think that could be our life, Ellie?” she quietly asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster smiled as she nestled her head into the crook of her partner’s neck, raised her hand, and kissed her fingertips.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“To me, it already is.”&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
