      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ah, The trail of love for Tricia Davenport has long since been deserted. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Carriage that rode along that road had long perished into the abyss of pain and divorce and was nothing more than a smattering of pieces. Real love was not to be found. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;At least that's what Tricia thought. Hard emphasis on Thought. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Being a live-in maid is only tough when you have worked for bless'ed Gabrielle for 9ish years. This woman will snap and bark like an angsty chihuahua whenever She doesn't get her way and..well..Ivan her nephew was her and Tricia's only bungee cord from swan diving straight into insanity over what the other did. Ivan's presence merely reduced it to just a teeter totter on the brink of insanity.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It is absolutely safe to say that neither saw it their way and Frankly it was getting old. Real, old. As the days stretched on, it became more evident that Tricia's work ethic was on life alert, at least in Gabrielle's opinion.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Gabrielle swore up and down that Tricia was just being lazy. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ivan Thought things were going swimmingly with a few tiffs, mistakes here and there. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Tricia wished she had a tall never-ending glass of Whiskey and Gabrielle would shut up already. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When Gabrielle finally had just about had it with Tricia's shenanigans and snapped like a brittle twig in the middle of November; She upped and hired a new maid with her precious money!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A Gorgeous Maid. A Capable Maid! A maid That wasn't Tricia!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But Right off the bat, something felt off to Tricia...Really off.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Why is it, As soon as She came around, She's got these 'weird' heart problems?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As soon as She came around, the stagnant pool of lust and longing akin to gasoline was set a lit. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As soon as she came around and stuck around, Those heart strings that she was sure had shriveled up and croaked? No longer weren't in a way She did. not. understand. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But amidst all these problems the doctor swore he couldn't diagnose, There were two promises Tricia made to herself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;To always care for her prized Horses and to never, ever fall for the love bullshit. It was the bachelor life from here on out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Or..was it?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
