      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Eddie has always been in awe of his best friend, Jason. By senior year, he's already hooked up with half the girls in their class. But when Jason pushes things too far, the girls make a pact, and he's left without a date for prom night. Luckily, he has a backup plan. That's where Eddie comes in. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Eddie never would've agreed to be Jason's backup girl. He's never felt that way about Jason, seriously. But Jason's so persistent. And so convincing. And so handsome...&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;So, fine. If Jason really needs a girl to make out with on prom night, Eddie will reluctantly play the part. Behind closed doors, anyway. But there's a few ground rules:&lt;br /&gt; 1. This will only happen once, and it definitely won't be a recurring thing that dominates their relationship for over a decade&lt;br /&gt; 2. Just because Eddie's wearing a dress doesn't mean he's going to have some big, life-ruining identity crisis&lt;br /&gt; 3. They are not going to fall in love&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;CWs for dysphoria and transphobia. Hope you enjoy!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
